<header class="header">
  <h1>Greenhouse Patch Tape vs Clear Tarp Tape</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    Both tapes can repair plastic, but they are designed for very different conditions.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most greenhouse repairs, greenhouse patch tape provides better adhesion and UV resistance, while clear tarp tape works as a short-term or lower-cost alternative.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    When greenhouse plastic tears, the repair needs to hold through sun exposure, temperature swings, and moisture. Not all tapes are designed for that level of stress.
  </p>
  <p>
    Choosing the right type of tape determines whether the repair lasts weeks or an entire season.
  </p>
</header>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Quick Answer: Which Should You Use?</h2>

  <div class="quickAnswerBox">
    <ul class="plainList">
      <li><strong>Best overall:</strong> greenhouse patch tape.</li>
      <li><strong>Best for quick fixes:</strong> clear tarp tape.</li>
      <li><strong>Best durability:</strong> UV-resistant patch tape.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>
    The main difference is long-term performance in outdoor conditions.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Greenhouse Patch Tape Does Better</h2>

  <p>
    Greenhouse patch tape is designed specifically for polyethylene greenhouse film and similar materials.
  </p>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li>strong adhesion to greenhouse plastic</li>
    <li>resists UV degradation</li>
    <li>holds through temperature changes</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    It is intended for repairs that need to last through a full growing season or longer.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Clear Tarp Tape Does Better</h2>

  <p>
    Clear tarp tape is more general-purpose and works across a variety of materials.
  </p>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li>easy to find and use</li>
    <li>lower cost</li>
    <li>good for temporary fixes</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    It works well for short-term repairs or emergency situations.
  </p>
</section>

