<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Use greenhouse patch tape for any repair you want to last through the season or longer. Use clear tarp tape only for temporary fixes or low-stress areas.
  </p>

  <p>
    Proper surface preparation and application make a significant difference in how well the repair holds.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Use the right tape for the job, and it will last.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    Greenhouse patch tape is the better choice for long-term durability and UV resistance, while clear tarp tape works best as a temporary solution.
  </p>

  <p>
    Matching the tape to the repair needs ensures better performance and fewer repeat fixes.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Long-term repairs need purpose-built materials.
